it's slides with code and output because I'm teaching code. So PowerPoint is maybe

00:00:56.759 --> 00:01:01.160
not the best option there, right? Even though otherwise it might be a great

00:01:01.160 --> 00:01:05.720
option. You need a website, probably. Somehow the students need to find all

00:01:05.720 --> 00:01:10.080
the materials. You need interactive exercises, at least that really enhances

00:01:10.080 --> 00:01:14.519
your class. You need student assignments. The students somehow need to be

00:01:14.519 --> 00:01:19.760
given something that they have to do, and maybe also you have like little shiny

00:01:19.760 --> 00:01:24.559
apps or so that just demonstrate some concept of your class, right? You may

00:01:24.559 --> 00:01:28.599
want that also. And we can do all of that in the R ecosystem, and like

00:01:28.599 --> 00:01:33.239
traditionally we had different packages like Scharingen for slides, and

00:01:33.239 --> 00:01:39.239
LearnR for interactive exercises, and so on. It all works fine, but honestly it's

00:01:39.239 --> 00:01:43.440
a hodgepodge of different technologies, and many of them can pose various

00:01:43.440 --> 00:01:47.599
challenges. And I've used them all, and I've run into challenges with all of

